### OpenAL ###

1. ENTITIES USED BY OPENAL

Listener
The person listening to the audio.

Source
The audiosource, e.g. speaker.

Buffer
The sound that's being played.

Device
The actual hardware that will be playing the sound, most likely analogous to the iPhone.

Context
The current session that all sounds will be played in.


2. BASICS TO PLAYING SOUNDS

The following steps are required to make the bare minimum work:
 1.  get the device.
 2.  create context with device.
 3.  put some data into the buffer.
 4.  attacks buffer to the source.
 5.  play the source.
 
